indicators.justification:
The framework prepared by the South African Legislative Sector does mention that information from participatory processes should be published on a relevant Ministry's website, and they also contemplate the use of social media (1). However, they do not explicitly refer to 'data'. They just use the word 'information'. So it is vague and not clear if they mean actual data or just the resolutions and outcomes from the sessions.

Sources;
(1)https://www.sals.gov.za/docs/pubs/ppf.pdf
